In Fig. 1, N depicts the number of active and energized sensor nodes in the network. Thus, the dimensions of each response vector will be equal to the number of active sensor nodes in a network since the cluster head selection process will be made from the energized nodes. Every active sensor device of the WSN has an assigned location in the response vector, as shown in Fig. 1. An integer value of 0 or 1 may be assigned to each position. The node that corresponds to the current location is chosen as a cluster head in this response if the position value is 1. If not, the associated node is not chosen as a cluster head. The list of nodes chosen as cluster leaders is initially saved in a set like C={c1,…, ci} in order to assess each response in the suggested method using the COA. Next, the following relationship is used to determine the fitness of the present selection:3\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
