This model has three input fuzzy variables, one output, and 18 fuzzy rules to determine the system output. The input variables used in this fuzzy system are: cluster centrality, distance to the base station, and average distance to other cluster heads. Centrality metric, whose membership functions are depicted in Fig. 3a, reflects the suitability of the cluster head’s position from a strategic perspective. A node with a suitable position plays a more effective role in shaping the data transmission paths towards the base station. For calculating the centrality of nodes, the adjacency graph of the network will be used. In this case, having the network’s adjacency matrix, the shortest paths between each node and the base station are extracted, and then the centrality of each node like i is calculated as follows:8\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
